               <history>
                  <origin>Undated, possibly <origDate cert="medium" calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1600" to="1700">17th century</origDate>.</origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>The circumstances under which the volume arrived in <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7008653" cert="high">Britain</placeName> remain unclear.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Apparently acquired by merchant and politician <persName role="fmo" key="person_f7938">Sir Gordon Fraser (1873–1934)</persName>, who was born in Manchester, but later lived in <placeName
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001797" key="place_7001797"
                        >Madras (Chennai)</placeName>Madras (Chennai) from 1895 until his death.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>After Fraser's death. given to the <orgName type="corporation" role="rps"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/">John Rylands Library</orgName> by his widow, <persName role="fmo" key="person_f7919">Lady Gordon Fraser</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1938-10">October, 1938</date>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
